      <bioghist id="aspace_7230d4297255eeade83ca5de73a9442e">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Hill. Louise Allison Cort (1944-) is a craft historian. Her B. Litt. thesis for Oxford University treated the 700-year history of a Japanese stoneware ceramic-producing community. Cort has also researched and published on the community of temple-servant potters in Puri, Odisha, India. She is Curator Emerita of ceramics at the National Museum of Asian Art of the Smithsonian Institution (Freer Gallery of Art and Arthur M. Sackler Gallery), where she curated large collections of both historical and contemporary ceramics in Southeast Asia.</p>
      </bioghist>
